I visited strictly to use the Wifi at this Dunkin' Donuts because I have had trouble in the past connecting with the Wifi at the Starbucks location attached to Jewel-Osco. I found other places in Wicker Park at the spare of the moment, but went with Dunkin' Donuts because I knew that there were seats available, and I was not too familiar with the other places I found, such as if they were congested or were there any parking spots near.  I visited this Dunkin' Donuts once in the past, only to leave instantly after noticing flies flying all in their donuts which I thought was disgusting, so I was a little hesitant on ordering their donuts during this visit.  I ordered a bacon egg & cheese bagel to eat while I wrote in my blog, which my order came in a timely manner that is typical to any Dunkin' Donuts location. Once I grabbed my order, the only seats I found were dirty! With that, I grabbed a few of their napkins to wipe the food particles off of the bench, which is very unsatisfactory for any customer to have to do at a restaurant. That alone gives me an idea of the work ethic the workers have at this location.  I have no problem on visiting this location in the future, but that would only be when I want to getaway from my neighborhood to utilize its Wifi, like such. Take what I have mentioned in consideration if you intend on visiting.  Thomas G
